  "detailed_description": "<p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Slide animals to save baby penguins and escape with walruses. Change the rules with simple items like a hammer, a spring, or a magnet. Discover  emergent uses of these tools, and how they interact with other mechanics. Explore an open world of nested puzzles by gaining new capabilities and knowledge.<br><br>Puzzles are designed to showcase with a \"simple, but difficult\" philosophy, with each puzzle bringing a new idea. They're carefully designed to be instructive, tight, and deducible.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2830480/extras/3ad32fc72b55af310b9c9150a663fec8.poster.avif?t=1770658152\" width=616 height=310 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2830480/extras/3ad32fc72b55af310b9c9150a663fec8.webm?t=1770658152\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2830480/extras/3ad32fc72b55af310b9c9150a663fec8.mp4?t=1770658152\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Featuring</h2><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > Penguins, walruses, and fish! Each introduces opposing win criteria.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Rapidly expanding set of mechanics and interactions.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Over 300 diverse, hand-crafted levels. No filler!</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > An interconnected network of puzzles with item-based progression and metagame twists.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > Journal for tracking mechanics, which also lists entries needed for the current puzzle.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > A tiered hint system that teaches a deduction-based approach.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >16 biomes distinguishing areas and mechanics, with original music.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Puzzle editor with Steam Workshop support for sharing custom levelpacks. </p></li></ul><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2830480/extras/6793075716b24e6526385b5c03f3a65c.poster.avif?t=1770658152\" width=616 height=310 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2830480/extras/6793075716b24e6526385b5c03f3a65c.webm?t=1770658152\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2830480/extras/6793075716b24e6526385b5c03f3a65c.mp4?t=1770658152\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Accessibility</h2><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > No time-sensitive inputs, with undo and redo binds that work through resets.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Use a controller, keyboard, or mouse with customizable binds. (Note: Puzzle editor requires a mouse.)</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > Colorblind friendly with customizable colors.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Most puzzles are optional for progression, and a setting makes any puzzle skippable.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Warp navigation system for quickly returning to anywhere you've been.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Solutions, [redacted], and [redacted]  are saved, so meta goals don't require any repeat work.</p></li></ul><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2830480/extras/bc7b957030f0860ff3956b8eb83b5702.poster.avif?t=1770658152\" width=616 height=310 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2830480/extras/bc7b957030f0860ff3956b8eb83b5702.webm?t=1770658152\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2830480/extras/bc7b957030f0860ff3956b8eb83b5702.mp4?t=1770658152\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></h2>",
  "about_the_game": "<p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Slide animals to save baby penguins and escape with walruses. Change the rules with simple items like a hammer, a spring, or a magnet. Discover  emergent uses of these tools, and how they interact with other mechanics. Explore an open world of nested puzzles by gaining new capabilities and knowledge.<br><br>Puzzles are designed to showcase with a \"simple, but difficult\" philosophy, with each puzzle bringing a new idea. They're carefully designed to be instructive, tight, and deducible.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2830480/extras/3ad32fc72b55af310b9c9150a663fec8.poster.avif?t=1770658152\" width=616 height=310 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2830480/extras/3ad32fc72b55af310b9c9150a663fec8.webm?t=1770658152\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2830480/extras/3ad32fc72b55af310b9c9150a663fec8.mp4?t=1770658152\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Featuring</h2><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > Penguins, walruses, and fish! Each introduces opposing win criteria.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Rapidly expanding set of mechanics and interactions.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Over 300 diverse, hand-crafted levels. No filler!</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > An interconnected network of puzzles with item-based progression and metagame twists.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > Journal for tracking mechanics, which also lists entries needed for the current puzzle.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > A tiered hint system that teaches a deduction-based approach.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >16 biomes distinguishing areas and mechanics, with original music.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Puzzle editor with Steam Workshop support for sharing custom levelpacks. </p></li></ul><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2830480/extras/6793075716b24e6526385b5c03f3a65c.poster.avif?t=1770658152\" width=616 height=310 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2830480/extras/6793075716b24e6526385b5c03f3a65c.webm?t=1770658152\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2830480/extras/6793075716b24e6526385b5c03f3a65c.mp4?t=1770658152\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Accessibility</h2><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > No time-sensitive inputs, with undo and redo binds that work through resets.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Use a controller, keyboard, or mouse with customizable binds. (Note: Puzzle editor requires a mouse.)</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > Colorblind friendly with customizable colors.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Most puzzles are optional for progression, and a setting makes any puzzle skippable.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Warp navigation system for quickly returning to anywhere you've been.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Solutions, [redacted], and [redacted]  are saved, so meta goals don't require any repeat work.</p></li></ul><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2830480/extras/bc7b957030f0860ff3956b8eb83b5702.poster.avif?t=1770658152\" width=616 height=310 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2830480/extras/bc7b957030f0860ff3956b8eb83b5702.webm?t=177065815